Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers state has commended the General Overseer of Omega Power Ministries OPM Apostle Chibuzor Chinyere over the commissioning of the Nyesom Wike Free Skill Acquisition Centre in the state. Governor Wike who was represented by his Chief of Staff Emeka Woke at the commissioning of the centre also urged other men of God to emulate the philanthropic attitude of Apostle Chibuzor Chinyere which has led to a drastic decrease in violence and other vices in the state as a result of the massive renunciation of criminality by former cultists, militants and armed robbers in the state. The State governor who also praised the efforts of Apostle Chibuzor in assisting citizens and residents of the state during the COVID 19 lockdown said with the commissioning of the centre, the state will pride itself of having one of the best skill acquisition centres in the country while also boosting manpower in the state and the country at large. The governor further promised to ensure that the state government will not hesitate to partner with organizations that are impacting on the lives of citizens thereby making them useful to their families. Speaking at the event, the General Overseer of the Omega Power Ministries OPM Aposle Chibuzor Gift Chinyere said he was moved by compassion to establish the Skill Acquisition centre which he says is part of his contribution among others to ensuring that members of the society especially perceived lost souls are won to Christ. He said the centre will help reduce the level of crime in the state and the country because most of the beneficiaries are repentant sex workers, cultists, armed robbers and militants who have decided to embrace Christ due to the humaneness of the Church which uses tithes and offerings of its members to touch lives and making them meaningful. Speaking further, the Welfare Director of the Omega Power Ministries OPM Dr. Maureen Chukwu said “The Nyesom Wike Skill Acquisition center trains people on various skills which includes scaffolding, oil and gas, tailoring, pipeline welding, computer operation, furniture making among others and it is completely free of charge for everybody not minding where they come from or the religion they profess” Recall that the OPM Foundation has been involved in a lot of philanthropic activities in the country which has seen it operating 15 free school programmes, free specialist hospital and the free skill acquisition centre that has trained more than five thousand youths since its inception in 2013 making it possible for graduates of the programme to be gainfully employed.